The paper deals with entity resolution in Knowledge Bases (KBs) and proposes a new framework called MinoanER that addresses challenges related to the Variety, Volume, and Veracity of entity descriptions in the Web of Data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.CL (computation and language). The paper's focus on similarity metrics, blocking methods, and matching algorithms also aligns with these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CL, in that order.
